# 6. First benchmark target

Use a narrow eval setup.

## Training source

* small curated reasoning set
* plus optional synthetic reasoning traces

## Proxy eval

* 50–100 reasoning problems
* exact match only
* single seed
* fast generation settings

## Confirmation eval

* 200–300 problems
* exact match
* 2 seeds

## Holdout eval

* frozen hidden subset
* only for finalists
* exact match
* 2 seeds

v1 success condition:

* evolved pipeline beats baseline by a real margin on holdout
* does not exceed compute budget
* survives multi-seed confirmation

---

# 7. Three-stage funnel

## Stage 1: cheap screen

Purpose: kill weak children fast.

* train_steps capped at 100–200
* tiny eval subset
* one seed
* no full artifact retention except logs and metrics

Promote roughly top 20–30%.

## Stage 2: medium validation

Purpose: check if signal persists.

* train_steps 400–800
* larger eval subset
* maybe 2 seeds for top few
* save adapter weights

Promote roughly top 10–20%.

## Stage 3: expensive confirmation

Purpose: determine survival / elite status.

* full configured train_steps
* full holdout
* multi-seed
* save all artifacts and report

Only a few finalists.

