# 21. Biggest mistakes to avoid

### Too many evolvable fields

Keep the genome small enough that search has signal.

### Weak holdout discipline

You need a real frozen holdout or the system will cheat.

### No cost penalties

It will drift toward slow, bloated pipelines.

### Saving too many artifacts

Disk and I/O will become a mess.

### Generalizing too early

Do not add multiple task families in month 1.

